article.headline: Canisius 70, Howard 46
article.story: WASHINGTON -- Greg Logins had 22 points and 14 rebounds to lead Canisius College to a 70-46 victory over Howard University on Monday night. Logins scored 10 points as Canisius (3-3) took control with a 17-4 run late in the first half. Logins shot 8 of 16 from the field and was perfect on six free throws in the Golden Griffins' first stop on a five-game road trip. Logins grabbed 12 of his rebounds on the offensive end and Canisius outrebounded Howard 56-25. Julius Coles and Frank Turner scored 13 points apiece for Canisius. Paul Kirkpatrick led Howard (1-5) with 12 points and eight rebounds. Eugene Myatt had 11 points and Calvin Thompson added 10. The victory was the first on the road this season for Canisius, which is playing a stretch of seven of nine games away from home.
